Qt for Python 6.11.0 is a minor release.

For more details, refer to the online documentation included in this
distribution. The documentation is also available online:

https://doc.qt.io/qtforpython/

Some of the changes listed in this file include issue tracking numbers
corresponding to tasks in the Qt Bug Tracker:

https://bugreports.qt.io/

Each of these identifiers can be entered in the bug tracker to obtain more
information about a particular change.

****************************************************************************
*                                  PySide6                                 *
****************************************************************************

  - QQmlComponent: Functions create_withownership() and
                   createWithInitialProperties_withownership() have been
                   added to return created QML objects with Python ownership.
 - [PYSIDE-2716] It is now possible to specify options for pyside6-uic and
                 pyside6-rcc in a pyproject.toml file. This is useful for
                 example to disable overly aggressive compression by
                 pyside6-rcc which may result in files that are not usable
                 on all platforms.
 - [PYSIDE-2786] The minimum supported Python version has been raised to
                 3.10.
 - [PYSIDE-3168] A number of examples have been updated for Qt 6.11.
 - [PYSIDE-3168] The QtCanvasPainter module and an example have been added.
 - [PYSIDE-3193] Type hints: The return type of QTranslator.translate()
                 has been fixed.
 - [PYSIDE-3257] pyside6-designer has been fixed to display Python help.
 - [PYSIDE-3273] A warning displayed when calling sys.exit() in
                 a overridden function has been suppressed.
 - [PYSIDE-3279] Signal emission has been sped up by code optimizations.
 - [QTBUG-131837] The QWebView class of QtWebView and an example
                  demoing it have been added.
 - [QTBUG-143503] It is now possible to populate QML views with JSON data as
                  shown in the updated colorpaletteclient example.

****************************************************************************
*                                  Shiboken6                               *
****************************************************************************

 - [PYSIDE-1587] The source tree has been restructured; the
                 shiboken-generator now is in a separate directory
                 to enable building with scikit-build.
 - [PYSIDE-2221] Some basic changes to enable free threaded Python/
                 subinterpreter support have been made.
 - [PYSIDE-2786] A number of helper functions now superseeded by Python 3.10
                 have been removed from libshiboken: _PepUnicode_AsString(),
                 PepType_GetSlot() and PepErr_GetRaisedException().
                 Shiboken::String::compare() has been deprecated.
 - [PYSIDE-3245] The support for synthesizing comparison operators in C++ 20
                 has been reimplemented and improved.
 - [PYSIDE-3245] Non-homogeneous reverse free comparison operators (trailing
                 class argument) are now ignored by the code generator,
                 potentially causing warnings about unmatched comparison
                 operator modifications. The warnings can be ignored, or,
                 the modification signatures can be rewritten to be
                 const member operators, which is the recommended way to
                 ensure compatibility with C++ 20 operator synthesis.
 - [PYSIDE-3105] The cross building support has been extended.
 - [PYSIDE-3155] libshiboken's warning/error messages are now prefixed.
 - [PYSIDE-3168] Only public static fields are generated (even with
                 the protected hack).
 - [PYSIDE-3253] A typesystem attribute to convert null smart pointers
                 to None has been added.
 - [PYSIDE-3282] Keyword arguments passed to base classes in case
                 of cooperative multiple inheritance are now filtered.
 - [PYSIDE-3285] Nested types have been removed from the generated module's
                 dictionaries.
